docs.text: the kids in the hall are an acquired taste .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it took at least a season of watching their show on hbo before i became a believer .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: maybe after watching a half dozen kids in the hall movies , they would grow into the big screen .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: my recommendation is that , unless you are a big fan of the kids , skip the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as it is , their first--and most likely only--attempt at a full length film lacks the qualities that made their comedy work on tv .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: a big-budget and glossy production can not make up for a lack of spontaneity that permeates their tv show .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the kids go through the motions , but you get the feeling that they arent really having fun doing so .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and this makes it more difficult for the audience to enjoy their antics .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: brain candy is a bunch of skits tied together by the story of a pharmaceutical company that develops a new drug to cure depression .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in typical sketch-comedy tradition , each actor plays several roles .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: doctor cooper ( kevin mcdonald ) and his team create the drug .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: then , under pressure from don roritor ( mark mckinney ) , founder and president of roritor pharmaceuticals , dr . cooper releases the drug into the marketplace .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the ensuing distribution of the new happy pill throughout the populace drives the rest of the film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: at about 90 minutes , brain candy still seems long .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the best thing about sketch comedy--and the kids are no exception--is the ability to quickly deliver the laughs , then go on to another quick skit .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: but with the additional set-up necessary in telling a longer , coherent story , the laughs just dont come fast enough .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: strangely , the show is even more tame than it was when on cable tv .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the movie makes several attempts at risqueness--mostly by pointing up the gayness of one of scott thompsons characters--but they seem almost forced ; as if they have to live up to a pg rating .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: one of the best bits , though , does make use of thompsons naked buttocks ; we see him charging into battle--going to have sex with some guys taking a shower .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in the classic of this genre , monty python pulled off this delicate balancing act between plot advancement and punchline delivery for most of the holy grail .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the kids , unfortunately , are not up to the task .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: there are some amusing moments , to be sure , but not enough to make the experience an enjoyable one .
